  > Wireshark
    > select interfaces
    > IP is at MAC
    > Statistics - Endpoints
  > ARP-Scan
    > sudo arp-scan -I <Interface> -g <local IP>/<CIDR>
  > Ping
    > ping <IP>
    > packets transmitted, received, packet loss, Error Message
  > fping
    > fping -I <Interface> -g <local IP>/<CIDR> -a (everything alive)
    > stderr 2 to /dev/null (2>/dev/null)
  > nmap
    > -sn (Ping Sweep Scan) <IP>/<CIDR>
  > zenmap (GUI Version of nmap)
    > Target like nmap (<IP>/<CIDR>)
    > Profile Ping Scan
   
